title: Why did ancient people build massive, mysterious mounds in Louisiana?
description: Hunter-gatherers at Poverty Point may have built its massive earthworks not under the command of chiefs, but as part of a vast, temporary gathering of egalitarian communities seeking spiritual harmony in a volatile world. New radiocarbon data and reexamined artifacts suggest far-flung travelers met to trade, worship, and participate in rituals designed to appease the forces of nature.

title: AI Unearths Ancient Life’s Chemical Ghosts, Reshaping Exoplanet Hunts
description: AI detects 3.3-billion-year-old microbial traces in Earth rocks, refining biosignature detection for exoplanets like JWST's K2-18b. Led by NASA astrobiologist Caleb Scharf, the method uncovers degraded chemical fingerprints, promising breakthroughs in alien life hunts.
